wikipedia_page.main: Edward Albert White (16 March 1844 – 3 May 1922) was an English first-class cricketer active 1867–75 who played for Kent. He was born in Yalding and died in Chiswick.

response: *Edward White (Australian politician) (1869–1959), member of the Victorian Legislative Council
*Edward White (Free-Church minister) (1819–1898), London Free Church minister
*Edward White (Medal of Honor) (1877–1908), Philippine–American War soldier and Medal of Honor recipient
He died at Tunbridge Wells in June 1917. His cousin Edward White was also a first-class cricketer.
